 account must be secured in a safe facility with access granted only in event of emergency.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E84Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E84Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.5\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E85\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Role based access control must be enforced on IAM accounts to ensure segregation of duties. For example, create a group for running network configuration scripts and a separate group for accessing hosts.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E85Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E85Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"Virtual Private Cloud (VPC)\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.6\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E86\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Privileges must be assigned to Groups and NOT individual accounts.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E86Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E86Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.7\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E87\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">VPCs must be designated either Production or non-production.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E87Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E87Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.8\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E88\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Production VPCs must be separate to non-production VPCs.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E88Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E88Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.9\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E89\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Access from the Internet to the VPC should be made unavailable by default; access to hosts in the VPC (from Internet) must be locked to specific (Optus or partner) IP addresses.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E89Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E89Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.10\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E810\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">The production VPC must be dedicated and not provide shared services. (I.e. dedicated to the specific project).</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E810Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E810Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.11\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E811\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Where possible, configuration of the VPC virtual infrastructure should be stored programmatically, so that version control and salvage of the infrastructure upon accidental deletion can be performed seamlessly.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E811Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E811Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.12\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E812\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">A management tier will be required in each VPC for management of components such as DNS, any monitoring tools, log collators, and for remote access and management of hosts in the VPC.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E812Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E812Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.13\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E813\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">If multiple VPCs are required:<br />- A Management VPC is recommended to centralise management components such as monitoring, DNS, and log data collection.<br />- Inter VPC communication should utilise AWS inter-VPC peering, and not the Optus internal network. <br />- Development VPCs should not be accessible from the Internet <br />- Test and QA VPCs will be a mirror of Production (with masked data) with No / limited Internet access, turned on as required to facilitate testing</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E813Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E813Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"Storage\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.14\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E814\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">If populating S3 storage with customer or other Sensitive information, server side encryption (AES 256) is required. This requires the client (customer \\\"OPTUS\\\") to hold and secure the symmetric key. See the following Amazon link for <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/aws.amazon.com\\/blogs\\/aws\\/s3-encryption-with-your-keys\\/\\\">how to deploy server side encryption with <\\/a>S3.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E814Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E814Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.15\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E815\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">The symmetric key must be stored securely locally (not on Amazon), not disclosed, and where possible changed routinely.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E815Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E815Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.16\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E816\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">S3 storage configuration must undergo security validation to ensure proper configuration before importing Sensitive data.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E816Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E816Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"Network\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.17\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E817\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">All internal hosts must use private IP addressing.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E817Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E817Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.18\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E818\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Interconnection between the VPC and Optus internal network must be over VPN or direct connect (if available).</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E818Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E818Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.19\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E819\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">The network within an Internet facing VPC must follow a three tier architecture layout, with a web/proxy, application and the database tier. See below.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E819Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E819Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.20\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E820\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">The VPCs internal network must maintain logical separation by deploying access control lists (ACL) and Security Groups to ensure subnets associated with one tier can only route to an adjacent tier. (For example, a host in the proxy tier should have no direct route to the database tier).</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E820Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E820Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.21\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E821\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Security Groups should be configured to allow only necessary communications between hosts. Configure Security Groups so that communications between hosts on any given tier are restricted at both the IP and UDP/TCP Port level. A host based firewalling may also be used for this purpose in place of Security Groups.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E821Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E821Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.22\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E822\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Within an Internet facing VPC, only servers in tiers 2 and 3 may communicate directly with the internal corporate network.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E822Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E822Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.23\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E823\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">Due to the dynamic nature of AWS IP addressing, hosts on a tier 2 or tier 3 network that require communication with the internal network must be deployed in their own dedicated subnet, and the corporate firewall configured to allow internal communication to that specified subnet.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E823Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E823Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										              \"value\": \"E.8.24\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textandcomments\",\n													  \"id\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E824\",\n										              \"value\": \"<p><span class=\\\"panel-span-medium\\\">A Web application Firewall (WAF) is required where an Internet facing VPC hosts Sensitive information or (if internally facing) accesses Sensitive information in the corporate network.</span></p>\"\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"radio\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E824Radio\",\n										              \"options\": [\n										                \"Yes\",\n										                \"No\",\n										                \"N/A\"\n										              ]\n										            },\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"textarea\",\n										              \"paramname\": \"CATPHAnnexEE8E824Comments\",\n										              \"rows\": \"2\"\n										            }\n										          ],\n										          [\n										            {\n										              \"type\": \"text\",\n										       